C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amazon%20is%20wreaking%20havoc%20on%20the%20ad%20market%2C%20and%20The%20Trade%20Desk%20may%20be%20its%20latest%20victim%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22LAS%20VEGAS%2C%20NEVADA%20-%20JANUARY%2006%3A%20(L-R)%20Jeff%20Green%2C%20Founder%2C%20CEO%2C%20and%20Chairman%2C%20The%20Trade%20Desk%20and%20Andrew%20Wallenstein%2C%20Variety%20Intelligence%20Platform%2C%20President%20and%20Chief%20Media%20Analyst%20speak%20onstage%20at%20%26quot%3BAdvertising's%20New%20Normal%3A%20Unifying%20Streaming%20and%20Identity%20in%202023%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20Variety%20Entertainment%20Summit%20at%20CES%20at%20the%20Aria%20Resort%20%26amp%3B%20Casino%20on%20January%2006%2C%202023%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20Nevada.%20(Photo%20by%20Greg%20Doherty%2FVariety%20via%20Getty%20Images)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68965b55f748d8c055f731d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Trade%20Desk%20CEO%20Jeff%20Green.%3Cp%3EGreg%20Doherty%2FVariety%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Trade%20Desk's%20shares%20plummeted%20nearly%2040%25%20and%20analysts%20blamed%20a%20growing%20rivalry%20with%20Amazon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20has%20expanded%20its%20ad%20business%20with%20a%20Roku%20deal%20and%20live%20sports%20on%20Prime%20Video.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnalysts%20expressed%20concern%20over%20The%20Trade%20Desk's%20prospects%20amid%20a%20competitive%20TV%20ad%20landscape.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trade%20Desk's%20shares%20cratered%20nearly%2040%25%20on%20Friday%2C%20its%20worst%20decline%20on%20record%2C%20and%20analysts%20say%20competition%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20be%20to%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-trade-desk-adtech-ad-cookies-uid-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrade%20Desk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20helps%20companies%20target%20people%20across%20the%20web%20with%20ads%2C%20beat%20expectations%20in%20its%20earnings%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20wasn't%20enough%20to%20quell%20Wall%20Street's%20concerns.%20In%20commentary%2C%20analysts%20also%20cited%20the%20departure%20of%20the%20adtech%20company's%20CFO%2C%20but%20largely%20focused%20on%20the%20Amazon%20factor%20in%20explaining%20the%20stock%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trade%20Desk%20CEO%20Jeff%20Green%20responded%20to%20analysts'%20questions%2C%20saying%20his%20company%20would%20continue%20to%20serve%20an%20important%20role%20because%20it's%20a%20neutral%20seller%20of%20advertising%2C%20unlike%20Amazon%2C%20which%20also%20sells%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-prime-video-preview-shake-up-tv-ad-marketplace-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eown%20ads%20on%20Prime%20Video%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20also%20argued%20The%20Trade%20Desk%20only%20competes%20with%20a%20small%20part%20of%20Amazon%20and%20suggested%20Amazon%20might%20one%20day%20allow%20companies%20like%20his%20own%20to%20sell%20ads%20on%20Prime%20Video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmazon%20is%20not%20a%20competitor%2C%20and%20Google%20really%20isn't%20much%20of%20a%20competitor%20anymore%20either%2C%26quot%3B%20Green%20said%20on%20the%20company's%20earnings%20call.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20trying%20to%20buy%20the%20open%20internet%2C%20leveraging%20technology%20that%20values%20media%20objectively.%20We%20don't%20have%20any%20media.%20And%20we%20don't%20grade%20our%20own%20homework.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20were%20skeptical%20of%20Green's%20optimistic%20stance%2C%20pointing%20to%20an%20increasingly%20competitive%20connected%20TV%20ad%20landscape.%20Amazon%2C%20Netflix%2C%20and%20Disney%2B%20have%20all%20entered%20the%20market%20in%20recent%20years.%20Amazon's%20ad%20business%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20on%20pace%20to%20grow%20fast%20with%20an%20upcoming%20deal%20to%20let%20advertisers%20buy%20ads%20on%20Roku%20devices%20through%20Amazon%2C%20and%20the%20NBA%20adding%20to%20Amazon's%20live%20sports%20programming%20on%20Prime%20Video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20The%20Trade%20Desk%20is%20limited%20in%20its%20growth%20potential%20because%20it%20depends%20on%20its%20ability%20to%20access%20the%20ad%20inventory%20of%20other%20players%20like%20Netflix.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELightShed%20analysts%20had%20the%20harshest%20words%2C%20writing%20that%20%26quot%3BGreen%20is%20either%20in%20a%20serious%20state%20of%20denial%2C%20or%20he%20is%20living%20in%20an%20alternate%20reality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Amazon%20shadow%20over%20this%20stock%20is%20now%20front%20and%20center%20...%20and%20harder%20to%20deny%2C%26quot%3B%20MoffettNathanson's%20Michael%20Nathanson%20said%2C%20cutting%20his%20rating%20to%20sell%20from%20neutral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20were%20more%20sanguine.%20Evercore%20maintained%20an%20outperform%20rating%2C%20citing%20The%20Trade%20Desk's%20growing%20partnerships%20to%20sell%20Netflix%2C%20Roku%2C%20and%20Spotify%20advertising%2C%20and%20its%20expansion%20in%20retail%20media%20and%20international%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228e8521b9-01e7-4be5-8b3f-4a960dfbc74b%5C%22%3EAmazon%20has%20become%20an%20ad%20titan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bull%20case%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ads-pitch-performance-tools-competition-with-netflix-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%3C%2Fa%3E%20ad%20business%20has%20been%20gaining%20steam%20since%20the%20company%20barrelled%20into%20the%20TV%20ad%20market%20a%20year%20ago%20by%20making%20ads%20the%20default%20on%20Prime%20Video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGripes%20about%20the%20ad%20rates%20notwithstanding%2C%20advertisers%20like%20Amazon's%20massive%20scale%2C%20ability%20to%20target%20people%20based%20on%20their%20shopping%20preferences%2C%20and%20growing%20live%20s