ct%3A%20A%20thin%20layer%20of%20film%20that%20sits%20on%20top%20of%20the%20brain.%3Cp%3EPrecision%20Neuroscience%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPrecision%20Neuroscience%20is%20developing%20a%20brain%20implant%20that%20sits%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20brain's%20cortex.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFounded%20by%20Neuralink%20alums%20in%202021%2C%20the%20company%20aims%20to%20bring%20a%20%26quot%3Bminimally%20invasive%26quot%3B%20BCI%20to%20market.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIts%20first%20goal%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Brestore%20independence%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20millions%20with%20paralysis.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20a%20city%20where%20high-stakes%20deals%20are%20made%20daily%2C%20few%20would%20expect%20that%20behind%20an%20unassuming%20Manhattan%20facade%20lies%20a%20team%20of%20neuroscientists%20developing%20a%20device%20that%20could%20change%20the%20relationship%20between%20machines%20and%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20change%20often%20hides%20in%20plain%20sight%2C%20undetectable%20until%20it%20isn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-rival-brain-implant-surgery-doesnt-need-to-be-invasive-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPrecision%20Neuroscience%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20developing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrain-computer-interface-what-is-it-how-does-it-work-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebrain-computer%20interface%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20system%20that%20creates%20a%20direct%20link%20between%20the%20brain's%20electrical%20activity%20and%20a%20computer.%20This%20type%20of%20technology%20has%20been%20in%20development%20for%20decades%2C%20but%20thanks%20to%20AI%2C%20the%20latest%20generation%20promises%20to%20reveal%20a%20wealth%20of%20new%20information%20about%20the%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20Precision's%20president%20and%20chief%20product%20officer%2C%20Craig%20Mermel%2C%20in%20March%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftakeaways-from-humanx-ai-conference-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ean%20AI%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20stood%20out%20as%20one%20of%20a%20few%20hardware%20companies%20among%20a%20sea%20of%20startups%20building%20productivity%20tools%20and%20coding%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20boom%2C%20Mermel%20told%20me%2C%20had%20turbocharged%20modern%20medicine's%20capacity%20to%20collect%20data%20about%20the%20brain.%20At%20a%20moment%20when%20many%20of%20the%20conference%20attendees%20talked%20about%20the%20technology's%20implications%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20broad%20terms%2C%20Mermel%20made%20them%20seem%20real%20%E2%80%94%20and%20imminent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrecision%20was%20founded%20in%202021%20by%20a%20group%20that%20included%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-elon-musk-microchips-brains-ai-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENeuralink%3C%2Fa%3E%20alums%2C%20including%20Ben%20Rapoport%2C%20a%20practicing%20neurosurgeon%20and%20electrical%20engineer%20who%20now%20serves%20as%20its%20chief%20science%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20initial%20goal%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Brestore%20independence%26quot%3B%20to%20severely%20paralyzed%20people%20in%20a%20less%20invasive%20way%20than%20its%20competitors%2C%20like%20Neuralink.%20That%20means%20helping%20those%20with%20paralysis%20communicate%20with%20others%2C%20use%20computers%2C%20or%20even%20hold%20a%20desk%20job%20by%20channeling%20their%20neural%20activity%20into%20commands%20for%20external%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20set%20of%20conditions%20that%20we're%20treating%20all%20have%20in%20common%20is%20paralysis.%20So%20it's%20people%20who%20basically%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20think%20like%20we%20do%2C%20but%20not%20the%20ability%20to%20move%2C%20especially%20move%20their%20hands%2C%26quot%3B%20Rapoport%20told%20me%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20the%20company's%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22345b436e-b176-486b-b14d-7d7d4f1e6510%5C%22%3EHow%20it%20works%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERapoport%20handed%20me%20a%20slip%20of%20yellow%20film%2C%20which%20the%20company%20calls%20the%20%26quot%3BLayer%207%20Cortical%20Interface.%26quot%3B%20The%20name%20reflects%20its%20ambitious%20goal%3A%20to%20create%20a%20seventh%20layer%20that%20sits%20atop%20the%20six%20cellular%20layers%20of%20the%20human%20cortex%2C%20the%20brain's%20outermost%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Precision%20Neuroscience%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6883eee3f748d8c055f65519%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHow%20the%20Layer%207%20Cortical%20Interface%20appears%20on%20the%20brain's%20surface.%3Cp%3EPrecision%20Neuroscience%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Layer%207%20Cortical%20Interface%20is%20about%20one-fifth%20the%20thickness%20of%20a%20human%20eyelash.%20One%20end%20is%20embedded%20with%20an%20array%20of%201%2C024%20electrodes%20that%20can%20record%20and%20stimulate%20brain%20activity.%20These%20electrodes%20have%20wires%20that%20run%20lengthwise%2C%20linking%20the%20film%20to%20custom%20electronics%20that%20process%20neural%20data%20and%20convert%20those%20signals%20into%20computer%20commands%20so%20patients%20can%20interact%20with%20the%20real%20world%20using%20thoughts%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20device%20is%20designed%20to%20rest%20on%20the%20brain's%20motor%20cortex%20%E2%80%94%20a%20small%20region%20located%20behind%20the%20frontal%20lobe%20that%20translates%20thoughts%20into%20actions%20%E2%80%94%20and%20conform%20to%20its%20surface%2C%20never%20directly%20damaging%20the%20tissue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20in%20place%2C%20it%20generates%20a%20detailed%20view%20of%20the%20brain's%20activity.%20Or%2C%20as%20Precision%20puts%20it%20on%20its%20website%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20world's%20highest%20resolution%20picture%20of%20human%20thought.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ade5868a-3321-479c-9544-946a1cca0e1d%5C%22%3EThe%20competition%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERapoport%20was%20part%20of%20the%20founding%20team%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-elon-musk-microchips-brains-ai-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENeuralink%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Elon%20Musk's%20high-profile%20neurotechnology%20venture.%20It%20launched%20in%202016%20and%20has%20raised%20about%20%241.3%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20PitchBook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20newsletter%20Neurotech%20Futures%20last%20year%20that%20he%20left%20Neuralink%20in%202018%20because%20brain-computer%20interface%20technology%20needed%20to%20be%20extremely%20safe%20and%20scalable%20for%20it%20to%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bclinical%20reality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20changes%20were%20needed%20in%20the%20way%20the%20technology%20was%20being%20implemented%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink's%20N1%20implant%20is%20a%20coin-sized%2C%20battery-powered%20device%20that%20sits%20on%20the%20skull%20and%20connects%20to%20ultra-thin%20threads%20%E2%80%94%20embedded%20with%20electrodes%20%E2%80%94%20that%20are%20woven%20into%20the%20brain's%20cortex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20April%202024%20update%20on%20its%20website%20about%20the%20status%20of%20its%20clinical%20trials%2C%20Neuralink%20detailed%20how%20the%20implant%20is%20inserted%20into%20the%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20a%20high%20level%2C%20the%20surgery%20involved%20a%20neurosurgeon%20exposing%20the%20target%20region%20of%20the%20cortex%20(e.g.%2C%20scalp%20incision%2C%20craniectomy%2C%20durectomy)%2C%20the%20R1%20Robot%20performing%20the%20insertions%20of%20threads%20of%20the%20N1%20Implant%2C%20and%20the%20neurosurgeon%20mounting%20the%20body%20of%20the%20N1%20Implant%20in%20the%20craniectomy%20and%20closing%20the%20scalp.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20follow-up%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Mermel%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20Neuralink's%20system%20is%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bpenetrating%20micro-electrodes%2C%20which%20cause%20damage%20when%20they're%20inserted%20into%20the%20brain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrecision%2C%20he%20said%2C%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bpossible%20to%20extract%20information-rich%20data%20from%20the%20brain%26quot%3B%20without%20damaging%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20Neuralink%20announced%20it%20had%20successfully%20completed%20implant%20surgeries%20on%20its%20eighth%20and%20ninth%20human%20patients.%20The%20company%20is%20expecting%20to%20implant%2020%2C000%20chips%20a%20year%20by%202031%20to%20generate%20at%20least%20%241%20billion%20in%20revenue%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2025-07-23%2Fneuralink-sees-1-billion-of-revenue-by-2031-in-vast-expansion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvasive%20forms%20of%20brain-computer%20interfaces%20typically%20involve%20implanting%20electrodes%20directly%20into%20the%20brain%20by%20way%20of%20a%20craniotomy%2C%20which%20involves%20removing%20a%20section%20of%20the%20skull%20to%20temporarily%20expose%20the%20brain%2C%20or%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecraniectomy%2C%20in%20which%20the%20removed%20bone%20is%20not%20replaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlackrock's%20Neurotech%2C%20which%20launched%20in%202008%2C%20makes%20a%20modified%20version%20of%20the%20Utah%20Array%20%E2%80%94%20a%20micro-electrode%20array%20that%20penetrates%20up%20to%201.5%20millimeters%20into%20the%20brain.%20It's%20been%20used%20for%20%26quot%3Bstudying%20neural%20circuits%2C%20investigating%20the%20mechanisms%20of%20brain%20function%2C%20and%20developing%20neural%20prosthetic%20devices%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Neurotech's%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESynchron%2C%20another%20company%20in%20the%20BCI%20race%2C%20makes%20a%20%26quot%3BStentrode%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20thin%2C%20flexible%20electrode%20array%20that%20doesn't%20require%20open-skull%20surgery.%20Instead%2C%20it's%20inserted%20into%20the%20brain%20through%20the%20jugular%20vein.%20Its%20aim%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Brestore%20control%20of%20a%20touchscreen%20in%20people%20with%20limited%20hand%20mobility%20using%20only%20their%20thoughts%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e7da4778-6380-4cb3-9ba4-8fd3aa008c28%5C%22%3EWhat's%20different%20about%20Precision%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Precision%20Neuroscience%20researcher%20holds%20the%20product%2C%20a%20thin%20film%20that%20sits%20on%20the%20top%20of%20the%20brain.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68964febcfc04e97619b22fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrecision%20Neuroscience%20says%20its%20first%20goal%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Brestore%20independence%26quot%3B%20to%20millions%20of%20people%20with%20paralysis.%3Cp%3EPrecision%20Neuroscience%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERapoport's%20thesis%20is%20that%20placing%20the%20device%20on%20the%20brain's%20surface%20itself%20is%20less%20invasive%20than%20its%20competitors%20and%20enough%20to%20gather%20valuable%20intel%20about%20how%20the%20brain%20operates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20think%20about%20the%20ways%20that%20we%20want%20the%20brain%20to%20interface%20with%20the%20digital%20world%2C%20most%20of%20what%20we%20think%20about%20is%20the%20conscious%20thought%20that%20takes%20place%20in%20the%20brain%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEssentially%20all%20of%20that%20takes%20place%20at%20the%20surface%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Boutermost%20few%20millimeters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20Layer%207%20Cortical%20Interface%20is%20designed%20to%20be%20easily%20replaced%20or%20moved.%20It's%20also%20modular%2C%20so%20multiple%20arrays%20can%20be%20combined%20to%20cover%20more%20regions%20of%20the%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20device%20is%20just%20one%20component%2C%20however.%20The%20method%20of%20insertion%20is%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrecision%20is%20also%20developing%20a%20minimally%20invasive%20%26quot%3Bcranial%20microslit%26quot%3B%20implant%20procedure%20to%20bypass%20the%20need%20for%20a%20full%20craniotomy%2C%20Mermel%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20by%20email.%20This%20involves%20making%20a%20small%20incision%2C%20less%20than%201%20millimeter%20into%20the%20skull%2C%20through%20which%20the%20Layer%207%20Cortical%20Interface%20is%20inserted%20and%20placed%20on%20the%20brain's%20surface%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225117faa6-3008-41c4-9528-a4366afc9cf7%5C%22%3EClinical%20studies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20FDA%20gave%20Synchron%20a%20green%20light%20to%20start%20clinical%20trials.%20In%202023%2C%20Neuralink%20received%20approval%20to%20start%20trials.%20Precision%2C%20at%20an%20earlier%20stage%20in%20its%20road%20to%20commercialization%2C%20announced%20its%20first%20clinical%20studies%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20the%20company%20has%20conducted%20clinical%20studies%20on%2047%20volunteer%20patients%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20whom%20were%20already%20undergoing%20brain%20surgery%20for%20other%20reasons.%20The%20devices%20were%20placed%20on%20their%20brains%20during%20surgery%20to%20read%2C%20record%2C%20and%20map%20activity%20on%20the%20brain's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20clinical%20studies%20%E2%80%94%20limited%20to%2015%20to%2030%20minutes%20%E2%80%94%20one%20or%20two%20electrode%20arrays%20were%20typically%20placed%20on%20a%20patient's%20brain%20while%20they%20engaged%20in%20activities%20such%20as%20speaking%2C%20playing%20rock-paper-scissors%2C%20or%20operating%20a%20joystick%2C%20so%20AI%20algorithms%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecould%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elearn%20the%20typical%20neural%20patterns%20associated%20with%20that%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20Precision%20said%20it%20received%20FDA%20clearance%20to%20use%20its%20electrode%20array%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Brecording%2C%20monitoring%2C%20and%20stimulation%20of%20electrical%20activity%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20brain.%26quot%3B%20The%20clearance%20authorizes%20the%20array%20for%20commercial%20use%20for%20up%20to%2030%20days.%20Studies%20are%20already%20underway%2C%20but%20the%20company%20declined%20to%20share%20the%20number%20of%20patients%20who%20are%20participating%20in%20these%20longer%20clinical%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Precision%20Neuroscience%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6883ef6ef748d8c055f6553c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrecision%20Neuroscience%20is%20mapping%20the%20electrical%20activity%20of%20the%20brain.%3Cp%3EPrecision%20Neuroscience%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd270b6c-5b4f-4def-a0d9-706e0f71b6ed%5C%22%3EThe%20value%20of%20the%20data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBrain-computer%20interfaces%20serve%20as%20translators%20of%20sorts%2C%20converting%20the%20brain's%20electrical%20language%20into%20the%20vernacular%20of%20machines%20%E2%80%94%20and%20eventually%2C%20into%20real-world%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrecision%20says%20its%20system%20captures%20about%201%20to%202%20billion%20data%20points%20per%20minute%20from%20each%20patient.%20It%20analyzes%20the%20data%20in%20real%20time%20and%20leverages%20AI%20algorithms%20to%20translate%20the%20raw%20data%20and%20electrical%20signals%20into%20computer%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20is%20to%20collect%20data%20from%20a%20diverse%20sample%20of%20patients%2C%20Rapoport%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20entire%20field%20of%20neuroscience%2C%20we%20have%20never%20had%20such%20a%20diverse%20set%20of%20high-quality%2C%20high-resolution%2C%20long-term%20recordings%20from%20dozens%20of%20patients'%20brains%20until%20we%20started%20doing%20this%2C%20and%20this%20includes%20Neuralink%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20all%20of%20its%20studies%2C%20it%20has%20gathered%20enough%20data%20to%20begin%20building%20what%20he%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bneural%20foundation%20model.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20focus%20of%20this%20machine%20learning%20model%20will%20be%20to%20decode%20speech%20and%20motor%20intention%20from%20the%20brain%20to%20ultimately%20help%20patients%20control%20computers%20and%20smartphones%2C%20Mermel%20said.%20However%2C%20he%20added%2C%20the%20company%20is%20exploring%20future%20use%20cases%20for%20its%20technology%2C%20including%20assisting%20surgeons%20during%20neurosurgery%2C%20treating%20conditions%20such%20as%20depression%2C%20and%20aiding%20in%20stroke%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20something%20that%20is%20safe%20and%20effective%20for%20a%20niche%20group%20of%20people%2C%20it%20begs%20the%20question%3A%20Are%20there%20ways%20to%20scale%20it%20beyond%20that%20original%20use%20case%3F%26quot%3B%20Rapoport%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprecision-neuroscience-neuralink-alums-brain-chip-bci-treatment-paralysis-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754681369000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68964217cfc04e97619b20b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprecision-neuroscience-neuralink-alums-brain-chip-bci-treatment-paralysis-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Precision%20Neuroscience%20says%20it%20may%20have%20a%20better%20way%20to%20restore%20independence%20to%20those%20with%20paralysis%20%E2%80%94%20by%20targeting%20the%20brain's%20surface.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40businessinsider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%